\par \pard\plain \s1\rtlch\af9\afs36\ab \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb400\sa200\keepn\ltrpar\cf19\f6\fs36\b\dbch\af9\pagebb\sb0\sa200{\rtlch\af9\afs36\ab \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\fs36\b\f5\dbch\af9\loch
10. Fund Governance & Social Impact}
\par \pard\plain \s2\rtlch\af9\afs28\ab \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb300\sa150\keepn\ltrpar\cf19\f6\fs28\b\dbch\af9\sb300\sa150{\rtlch\af9\afs28\ab \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\fs28\b\f5\dbch\af9\loch
10.1 The Educational Fund}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs22\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\f4\fs22\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af8\langfe2052\sl-276\slmult0\ql\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af8\afs22 \ltrch\loch\cf18\fs22\dbch\af8\loch
A dedicated Educational Fund will be created from UMOJA-ai revenue. This fund represents a transformational element of the model: for the first time, the education system itself generates the income needed to sustain and improve its operations. The fund will finance school infrastructure improvements (buildings, furniture, sanitation, electricity), learning materials (textbooks, exercise books, laboratory equipment), teacher supplementary payments and professional development, scholarship programs for exceptional students, and technology upgrades and expansion.}
\par \pard\plain \s2\rtlch\af9\afs28\ab \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb300\sa150\keepn\ltrpar\cf19\f6\fs28\b\dbch\af9\sb300\sa150{\rtlch\af9\afs28\ab \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\fs28\b\f5\dbch\af9\loch
10.2 Independent Administration}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs22\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\f4\fs22\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af8\langfe2052\sl-276\slmult0\ql\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af8\afs22 \ltrch\loch\cf18\fs22\dbch\af8\loch
The fund will be administered by an independent company established specifically for this purpose. This entity will work closely with both the Government of Ghana and UMOJA-ai but will maintain operational independence to ensure transparent, accountable management of resources. Governance will include an independent board of directors with representation from government, UMOJA-ai, civil society, and education professionals, annual external audits published publicly, clear investment policies and disbursement procedures, and regular reporting to all stakeholders.}
\par \pard\plain \s2\rtlch\af9\afs28\ab \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb300\sa150\keepn\ltrpar\cf19\f6\fs28\b\dbch\af9\sb300\sa150{\rtlch\af9\afs28\ab \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\cf19\fs28\b\f5\dbch\af9\loch
10.3 Social Impact Metrics}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs22\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\f4\fs22\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af8\langfe2052\sl-276\slmult0\ql\sb0\sa120{\rtlch\af8\afs22 \ltrch\loch\cf18\fs22\dbch\af8\loch
Beyond financial returns, UMOJA-ai commits to measuring and reporting on learning outcome improvements across all deployed schools, dropout rate reductions, gender parity in enrollment and achievement, rural-urban achievement gap narrowing, teacher satisfaction and professional development outcomes, and infrastructure improvements funded by the Educational Fund.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af8\afs22\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1033\langfe2052\hich\af4\loch\ql\widctlpar\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\ql\widctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\cf0\f4\fs22\lang1033\kerning0\dbch\af8\langfe2052\loch

